or only four-foot-two
It could happen ♪

02:01.329 --> 02:05.707
♪ I got a blind date
waiting to come around
Ooh-hoo, ooh-hoo ♪

02:05.792 --> 02:09.294
♪ Any minute now
Oy, but I'm nervous
Listen to my heart pound ♪

02:09.378 --> 02:11.797
♪♪ [Drum]
♪ Boom, Dee, boom
Boom, Dee, boom, boom, Dee ♪

02:11.881 --> 02:14.299
♪ Why do I need this headache ♪

02:14.384 --> 02:17.052
♪ Single is not a crime ♪

02:17.137 --> 02:19.972
♪ I got a blind date
and with my luck ♪

02:20.056 --> 02:22.766
♪ He'll come on time ♪

02:22.851 --> 02:26.228
[Laughing]

02:27.564 --> 02:30.732
♪ I got a girlfriend Shirley
who says, why not ♪

02:30.817 --> 02:33.026
[Laughs]
♪ She's an idiot ♪

02:33.111 --> 02:35.696
♪ This guy's a friend from
a friend of a friend she got ♪

02:35.780 --> 02:38.157
Hello. How do you do?
♪ What an idiot ♪

02:38.241 --> 02:40.576
♪ What do I need from Shirley ♪

02:40.660 --> 02:43.203
♪ Her and her 50 cup ♪

02:43.288 --> 02:48.458
♪ I got a blind date and
I'm praying he stands me up ♪

02:48.543 --> 02:51.461
Wait, wait. What am
I praying, he stands me up?
I'll stand him up!

02:51.546 --> 02:54.423
I smell a rat anyway.
I'm gonna hide under the bed.

02:54.507 --> 02:56.425
He'll walk in.
He'll never see me.

02:56.509 --> 02:58.260
He'll look around.
I wouldn't be there.

02:58.344 --> 03:00.554
He'll go away, and that's
the end of that. Perfect!

03:00.638 --> 03:03.557
Now, you keep quiet.
Not a word, ya hear?
Ya didn't see a thing.

03:03.641 --> 03:06.268
[Knocking]
Oh, oh, oh!
There he is!

03:06.352 --> 03:09.521
Okay, shh‒ quiet, everybody.
Shh‒ quiet.

03:09.606 --> 03:11.607
♪♪ [Orchestra]

03:14.485 --> 03:17.738
Rosalie?
She doesn't seem to be here.

03:17.822 --> 03:21.116
Well, that's never
happened to me before.

03:21.201 --> 03:23.202
It worked! It worked!
He never saw me.

03:23.286 --> 03:28.624
Boy, am I lucky. I didn't see
him neither, but I could just
imagine what a lox that one was.

03:28.708 --> 03:31.460
[Laughing]
Wait a minute.
What? What?

03:31.544 --> 03:33.462
He looked like Rudolph.
Rudolph who?

03:33.546 --> 03:36.215
Rudolph Valentino!
Get away!

03:36.299 --> 03:41.094
That's right.
Wait a minute. Is this person
kidding me around here?

03:41.179 --> 03:43.722
No!
[Laughing]

03:43.806 --> 03:48.018
Get away. Hmm.

03:48.102 --> 03:52.898
Well, that's what happened.
I let him get away.

03:52.982 --> 03:57.861
♪ What'll I do now
Maybe become a nun ♪

03:57.946 --> 04:00.155
That's impossible.

04:00.240 --> 04:04.368
♪ I'm callin' Shirley
Maybe she'll bring a gun ♪

04:04.452 --> 04:09.623
♪ Please, Shirley
Even if he's Lon Chaney ♪

04:09.707 --> 04:12.376
♪ Fat, bald or short or tall ♪

04:12.460 --> 04:16.213
♪ Having a blind date's
better than having no date ♪

04:16.297 --> 04:18.339
Ow!
♪ At no time ♪

04:18.423 --> 04:23.303
♪ With no one at all ♪♪

04:23.388 --> 04:26.640
Ohh! He's cute.
Hello there.

04:26.724 --> 04:30.769
Oh, my God! Oh, Shirley.

04:30.853 --> 04:32.771
[Applause]
Thank you.

04:32.855 --> 04:35.857
I can't find him.

04:35.942 --> 04:37.859
[Applause]

04:41.948 --> 04:44.533
He said he'd be here before
the finale. Where is he?

04:44.617 --> 04:48.328
Fanny, honey,
he said if he could
make it here tonight,

04:48.413 --> 04:51.290
he would try to get here
before the finale.

04:51.374 --> 04:54.793
He'll be here.
Don't get your hopes up
too high.

04:54.877 --> 04:57.254
Thanks for everything, Fanny.
I hate to see the show close.

04:57.338 --> 04:59.298
We'll do
another one soon.
I hope so.

04:59.382 --> 05:01.842
See you on the breadline.

05:05.430 --> 05:07.723
Yeah. Yeah.

05:09.142 --> 05:12.227
Mmm! Ooh.

05:13.354 --> 05:16.523
Oh, I told you.
I told you, Adele.

05:16.607 --> 05:21.069
"I'll always love you."
He'll always love me.

05:21.154 --> 05:24.865
Mmm!
Uh, Fanny, uh‒

05:24.949 --> 05:28.535
Nick didn't come
with the flowers.

05:30.246 --> 05:33.707
This did.

05:33.791 --> 05:37.377
I'm afraid it's
pumpkin time, princess.

05:39.881 --> 05:41.882
[Applause]

05:50.266 --> 05:53.727
Why don't you go
pass out the...

05:53.811 --> 05:57.022
presents to the kids,

05:57.106 --> 06:01.777
before the booze eats
its way out of the bottles?

06:06.240 --> 06:09.951
[Door Opens, Closes]

06:13.456 --> 06:16.541
Easy come, easy go.

06:16.626 --> 06:18.668
Fanny...
Out! Out!

06:18.753 --> 06:21.713
If you're gonna sob,
do a single.

06:43.736 --> 06:47.823
[Fanny's Voice]
♪ Nicky Arnstein ♪

06:47.907 --> 06:51.201
♪ Nicky Arnstein ♪♪

07:02.213 --> 07:05.799
Anything coming up?
Anything at all?

07:05.883 --> 07:10.887
Oh, yeah. Yeah, I've auditioned
for a couple of things.
Mm-hmm.

07:10.972 --> 07:13.432
I'm scared, Fanny.

07:13.516 --> 07:16.935
I think I'm getting
to be a little too, uh,

07:17.019 --> 07:19.521
distinguished to go on
shaking it around.

07:19.605 --> 07:23.108
You know what I mean?
[Chuckles]

07:23.192 --> 07:25.986
How many shows
we been in together, Bobby?
Oh, s‒

07:26.070 --> 07:27.988
Six?
Oh, easy.

07:28.072 --> 07:31.283
Yeah. You knew me...

07:31.367 --> 07:33.410
before Nick,

07:33.494 --> 07:36.830
during Nick, after Nick.

07:36.914 --> 07:39.458
You're always doing
this for me, that for me.

07:39.542 --> 07:42.627
It's time I started
paying you for it someway.

07:42.712 --> 07:45.839
Hey, Fanny,
I'm not really...

07:45.923 --> 07:48.800
Maybe you're not really,
but I am really...

07:48.885 --> 07:51.720
What is that
supposed to mean?
How do I know?

07:51.804 --> 07:54.347
I got the willies too.
The show closing‒

07:54.432 --> 07:56.850
Hey, can you balance
a checkbook?

07:56.934 --> 07:59.060
Well, now, you know,
I bet I could,

07:59.145 --> 08:01.062
if somebody
showed me how.
Yeah.

08:01.147 --> 08:04.566
You don't have to offer
me a job. I couldn't
take money from you.

08:04.650 --> 08:07.652
Who's offering you money?
You think I got any money?

08:07.737 --> 08:09.654
We'll all be back
in here soon.

08:09.739 --> 08:13.992
You bet we will, Ben.
You better start getting
the gum off the seats.

08:14.076 --> 08:16.328
Hey, I got
a terrific idea.
What?

08:16.412 --> 08:20.665
Move into my place, Bobby.
No pay, but room and
"board" you won't be.

08:20.750 --> 08:23.627
I think we can help each other.
I mean it.

08:23.711 --> 08:27.005
I'm going to say
something stupid.

08:27.089 --> 08:29.674
I know a little of what
you're going through,

08:29.759 --> 08:33.303
'cause, you see,
I miss Nick too.

08:33.386 --> 08:37.097
So I do know a little bit
of what it's like.

08:37.183 --> 08:40.227
Now, it's just
a matter of time, Fanny.

08:40.311 --> 08:42.437
Yeah, and Nick's pride.

08:42.522 --> 08:46.858
He will make a comeback,
and when he does,
you'll be there.

08:46.943 --> 08:50.904
Yeah. I ain't
goin' nowhere, kid,
except home.

08:50.988 --> 08:56.284
Come on, come on, come on.
Come on. I'll race ya.
[Laughs]

08:56.369 --> 09:00.288
When do you start
the new Follies?

09:00.373 --> 09:02.499
He can't raise
the money, Barney.

09:02.583 --> 09:07.504
Ziegfeld can't
raise the money?
Not even from Buck?

09:07.588 --> 09:10.966
Things are tough all over.
Even the grocer
is suing us.

09:11.050 --> 09:15.136
It's going to look lousy
going to court over
cornflakes and toilet paper.

09:15.221 --> 09:19.891
Fanny, darling, I think
I'd better make you a loan.

09:19.976 --> 09:23.645
Barney, "dollink," I think
I'd better sell my house.
What do you think I can get?

09:23.729 --> 09:26.898
Not anywhere near
what it's worth‒
not in this market,

09:26.983 --> 09:30.235
and not with
the mortgage it carries.
What about a second mortgage?

09:30.319 --> 09:32.153
What about a loan?

09:32.238 --> 09:34.698
What's the use of borrowing?
I just have to give it back.

09:34.782 --> 09:38.493
- Of course,
there are Fran's holdings.
- I didn't hear it.

09:38.578 --> 09:40.495
[Woman] I told you
Mr. Baruch was engaged—
[Man] It's all right.

09:40.580 --> 09:42.247
He'll understand.
He's got an
important client.

09:42.331 --> 09:45.500
I'm sorry.
There's a very important meeting.
No interruptions.

09:45.585 --> 09:50.088
Oh, I do apologize, Mr. Baruch.
Excuse me for
busting in like this.

09:50.172 --> 09:53.091
I brought you this milk shake.
I wanted to get it to you
before it lost its foam.

09:53.175 --> 09:56.595
Sorry to bust in on you
like this, Miss Brice.

09:56.679 --> 10:00.807
I hope the milk shake's
not C.O.D., kid.
[Laughs]

10:00.891 --> 10:04.811
Now that we're all here,
is there anything
I can do for ya?

10:04.895 --> 10:07.314
Fanny, Mr. Rose
is a man of many parts.

10:07.398 --> 10:11.109
Among other things,
he's a champion speed-writer,
200 words a minute.

10:11.193 --> 10:13.737
We were just
going over Miss Brice's
daughter's holdings.

10:13.821 --> 10:16.865
Maybe I can be of some help.
Do you mind?

10:16.949 --> 10:19.117
Why should I mind?
Great.

10:19.201 --> 10:21.161
[Clattering]
So I‒
[Laughs]

10:21.245 --> 10:25.165
I'm so‒
I'd like to make
a few suggestions for Fran.

10:25.249 --> 10:28.168
This is rough,
but I think you should
take a few more losses.

10:28.252 --> 10:31.880
These will only go lower,
so I'd sell...

10:31.964 --> 10:34.049
American Hide and Leather,
bought at 34, now 81/2.

10:34.133 --> 10:36.885
AT&T, bought at 158,
now 111.

10:36.969 --> 10:38.803
Celutex, bought at 60,
now 3.

10:38.888 --> 10:42.140
From 60 to 3?
Keep it. We shouldn't cause
Celutex more aggravation.

10:42.224 --> 10:44.893
Cuban American Sugar,
bought at 21, now 3.

10:44.977 --> 10:47.228
Elkhorn Coal, bought at
five 1/2, now 1/8.

10:47.313 --> 10:49.230
Elkhorn Coal. It figures.

10:49.315 --> 10:52.025
Noranda Mines,
bought at 17, now 17.

10:52.109 --> 10:54.402
Bought at 17, still 17?
That's a winner.

10:54.487 --> 10:58.156
Maracaibo Oil, bought at 103,
now one and three-quarters.

10:58.240 --> 11:01.117
Pennsylvania Coal and Coke,
bought at 121/2, now 4.

11:01.202 --> 11:03.828
Sell, sell, before
they wipe my kid out.

11:03.913 --> 11:06.164
Billy, did you get it?

11:06.248 --> 11:08.541
"American Hide and Leather,
bought at 34, now 81/2.

11:08.626 --> 11:12.128
"AT&T, bought at 158,
now 111.
Celutex bought at 60, now 3.

11:12.213 --> 11:14.756
"From 60 to 3?
Keep it. We shouldn't cause
Celutex more aggravation.

11:14.840 --> 11:16.758
"Cuban American Sugar,
bought at 21, now 3.

11:16.842 --> 11:19.552
"Elkhorn Coal, bought
at five 1/2, now 1/8.
Elkhorn coal. It figures.

11:19.637 --> 11:21.346
"Noranda Mines,
bought at 17, now 17.

11:21.430 --> 11:23.348
"Bought at 17, still 17?
That's a winner.

11:23.432 --> 11:25.517
"Maracaibo Oil, bought at 103,
now one and three-quarters.

11:25.601 --> 11:27.686
"Pennsylvania Coal and Coke,
bought at 121/2, now 4.

11:27.770 --> 11:30.689
Sell, sell, before
they wipe my kid out.
Billy, did you get it?"

11:30.773 --> 11:34.651
That about sums it up.
There's an act
in there somewhere.

11:34.735 --> 11:37.362
Now, if you'd allow me
to make you a loan?

11:37.446 --> 11:39.489
Thanks, Barney.
Thank you for seeing me.

11:39.573 --> 11:44.494
Anytime, my dear.
Anytime.
Come on, Bobby.

11:44.578 --> 11:46.871
Nice seeing you
again, Bobby.
Same here.

11:46.956 --> 11:50.041
Uh, listen, uh‒

11:50.126 --> 11:55.171
Miss Brice, hang‒
hang on to that AT&T, huh?
Believe me.

11:57.007 --> 11:59.259
[Clacking]

12:00.886 --> 12:03.096
Who's the pansy?

12:03.180 --> 12:05.098
Mr. Moore is
Miss Brice's secretary now.

12:05.182 --> 12:07.559
He's a very old friend,
from the days with Nick.

12:07.643 --> 12:10.687
Oh. She should have
taken a loss.

12:10.771 --> 12:14.691
[Gasps]
Look at this child.
That was gorgeous, sweetheart!

12:14.775 --> 12:16.985
You'd better get
out there and hustle.

12:17.069 --> 12:19.279
Get an act together.
Play the Palace.
Why don't you cut a record?

12:19.363 --> 12:23.324
Who can afford to put together
an act? It takes money. Where
am I going to get new material?

12:23.409 --> 12:26.411
I know what we should do.
Get all duded up.
Go around to all the spots.

12:26.495 --> 12:28.705
Fran.
[Speaks French]

12:28.789 --> 12:31.124
Merci beaucoup,
monsieur Cornell.
[Sniffs]

12:31.208 --> 12:35.628
Oh, mon Dieu.
[French]

12:35.713 --> 12:40.592
Right, right.
Wonderful, wonderful.
Ah.

12:40.676 --> 12:43.678
What'd she say?
It makes her mad
when I let my nose drip.

12:43.763 --> 12:48.308
Oh, so you mean
anytime my nose drips‒
anytime my nose drips...

12:48.392 --> 12:50.643
I have to say,
"mouce mi name"?
Yeah.

12:50.728 --> 12:54.314
Let's do like I said, huh?
Go out and tour the clubs.

12:54.398 --> 12:59.027
Catch all the acts
and just see if there's
anything we can borrow.

12:59.111 --> 13:02.363
[Woman]
♪ Oh, how I'd cry ♪

13:02.448 --> 13:06.493
♪ Oh, how I'd cry ♪
Excuse me, Miss Brice.
May I seat you?

13:06.577 --> 13:09.037
♪ If you got tired ♪

13:09.121 --> 13:12.290
♪ And said good-bye ♪

13:12.374 --> 13:15.126
♪ More than I'd show ♪

13:15.211 --> 13:17.754
♪ More than you'll ♪

13:17.838 --> 13:24.135
♪ Ever ♪

13:24.220 --> 13:28.556
♪ Know ♪♪

13:29.934 --> 13:31.976
This way, please.

13:34.939 --> 13:37.273
Oh, there's Fanny Brice.

13:39.902 --> 13:42.487
Why don't you find out
who wrote that song?

13:42.571 --> 13:46.157
Oh, yeah, sure.
Order me a stinger, huh?
Okay.

13:46.242 --> 13:49.619
Hey, Buck, how are ya?
Bobby. Fanny!

13:49.703 --> 13:53.957
Buck! How are
they running?
Dandy. It's good to see ya.

13:54.041 --> 13:56.501
I'd like you to meet
Miss Norma Butler.

13:56.585 --> 13:59.963
Glad to meet you.
It's a thrill to meet you.

14:00.047 --> 14:03.466
Nice set of beads.
Thank you.

14:03.551 --> 14:06.803
[Laughs]
Fanny, I'll call you.
Okay.

14:06.887 --> 14:09.180
Let's go, baby.
Bye.

14:09.265 --> 14:11.307
♪♪ [Piano]
[Clears Throat]

14:11.392 --> 14:15.186
Hey there, Miss Brice.
How are ya, huh?

14:15.271 --> 14:19.148
That was quite an entrance
you made. You really know
how to part the waters.

14:19.233 --> 14:21.734
It ain't difficult to part
the waters in a bathtub.

14:21.819 --> 14:24.279
Well, it's a small thing,
but my own.

14:24.363 --> 14:26.281
Oh, yeah?
Yeah.

14:26.365 --> 14:29.325
Good for you.
Hello there, Joe.

14:29.410 --> 14:33.872
You don't remember me, huh?
From Mr. Baruch's office.

14:33.956 --> 14:37.208
"Sell, sell."
Did you hang on to AT&T
like I told you?

14:37.293 --> 14:39.210
Oh, yeah, I did.

14:39.295 --> 14:42.463
That's good.
And, kid,
you better be right.

14:42.548 --> 14:46.050
I'm always right.

14:46.135 --> 14:49.387
You got some ashes
on your jacket.
Oh.

14:49.471 --> 14:52.557
Last time I saw you,
you were working
for Barney Baruch,

14:52.641 --> 14:56.269
very respectable,
and now suddenly you're
in the clip business?

14:56.353 --> 14:59.105
Not so suddenly.

14:59.189 --> 15:01.774
I haven't worked
for Mr. Baruch in years.

15:01.859 --> 15:04.527
We're just friends.

15:04.612 --> 15:06.946
You mind, uh‒
No, go right ahead.

15:08.991 --> 15:12.660
How do ya‒
Oh, excuse me.

15:12.745 --> 15:16.539
Comme ça.
Ah, thank you.
That's cute.

15:16.624 --> 15:19.667
You know, to tell you
the truth, uh‒

15:19.752 --> 15:23.004
I knew you were
in that office that day.

15:23.088 --> 15:26.382
I just wanted
to meet you. Hmm.

15:27.801 --> 15:30.553
♪♪ [Piano]
Waiter.

15:30.638 --> 15:33.932
One scotch
and water, please,
and, uh, one stinger.

15:34.016 --> 15:37.018
What'll you have?
The drinks are
on the house, huh?

15:37.102 --> 15:39.020
Bring me the usual.

15:39.104 --> 15:41.481
What's the usual?
Something you stir up
in the back room?

15:41.565 --> 15:44.817
I drink celery tonic.
You drink celery tonic?

15:44.902 --> 15:47.320
My mother said,
"A boozer is a loser."

15:47.404 --> 15:50.573
You had a mother?
[Laughs]

15:50.658 --> 15:55.370
So how'd you
get from Baruch
to here, and why?

15:55.454 --> 15:58.706
Maybe I wanted to wear
a black hat and meet girls.
You like the girls, huh?

15:58.791 --> 16:00.708
Sorry I took so long.
Me too.

16:00.793 --> 16:05.838
The guy who wrote
that song runs this club.
His name's Rose.

16:05.923 --> 16:08.424
Here.

16:08.509 --> 16:10.885
Is that a fact?

16:12.262 --> 16:14.514
Bobby, I'm sorry.

16:14.598 --> 16:17.308
You remember Mr. Rose here
from Baruch's office?

16:17.393 --> 16:20.812
Oh! Oh, yeah, sure.

16:20.896 --> 16:24.148
I didn't recognize you
without your milk shake.

16:24.233 --> 16:28.486
You really write that number
"More Than You Know"?

16:28.570 --> 16:31.155
Miss Brice, I wrote
"More Than You Know"
before breakfast.

16:31.240 --> 16:34.534
"When a Woman Loves a Man,"
I wrote that before I put
the cream in my coffee.

16:34.618 --> 16:36.869
Okay, swifty,
I get the message.
I might like to record it.

16:36.954 --> 16:40.790
Maybe we can get together
on a second number.
I'm sure we can.

16:40.874 --> 16:45.837
I have three numbers I think
would be terrific for ya.

16:45.921 --> 16:51.092
Unfortunately,
I promised them
to Ruth Etting.

16:51.176 --> 16:53.886
Maybe I can get one
of them back. I don't know.
It won't be easy.

16:53.971 --> 16:57.974
If I do,
I'll let you have it
for what Etting pays,

16:58.058 --> 17:01.394
which is one-third
off my usual price,
'cause I like the broad.

17:01.478 --> 17:05.314
To tell you the truth,
I feel a little sorry for her.

17:05.398 --> 17:08.358
Do you believe
your ears?

17:08.444 --> 17:13.865
Kid, new songwriters usually
pay me to record their stuff.

17:13.949 --> 17:17.577
Well, I ain't that new.

17:17.661 --> 17:19.871
I'll tell you the truth.

17:19.954 --> 17:22.205
"More Than You Know"
I don't like
well enough to buy.

17:22.290 --> 17:25.167
I only like it
well enough to steal.

17:25.252 --> 17:27.920
That's exactly what
I said in the first place.

17:28.005 --> 17:30.465
"More Than You Know"
is a definite literal steal.

17:30.549 --> 17:32.925
But take it. It's yours.
I don't want to talk about that.

17:33.010 --> 17:36.345
I want to talk about the other
number. The one I got in mind
for you, you're gonna love it.

17:36.430 --> 17:39.891
